==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[γραμμα]]'' meaning "a letter" and ''[[φωνη]]'' meaning "a sound", coined by [[w:Emile Berliner|Emile Berliner]] after the invention of the first [[phonograph]]

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''gramophone'''
#{{obsolete}} a [[record player]], an instrument for recording or reproducing sounds especially characterized by recording on a disk rather than a cylinder.

===Derived terms===
*[[gramophone record]]
